nn 2_16_intermediate_value_theorem
ln Intermediate Value Theorem.
ln Suppose $f$ is continuous on the interval $[a, b]$ and $L$
ln is a number strictly between $f(a)$ and $f(b)$. Then there
ln exists at lest one number $c$ in $(a, b)$ satisfying $f(c) = L$.
ff Intermediate Value Theorem
fb Suppose \(f\) is continuous on the interval \([a, b]\) and \(L\)
fb is a number strictly between \(f(a)\) and \(f(b)\). Then there
fb exists at lest one number \(c\) in \((a, b)\) satisfying \(f(c) = L\).

nn 3_10_trigonometric_limits
ln Trigonometric Limits.
ln $$\
ln \lim_{x \to 0} = {\sin x \over x} = 1
ln $$
ln 
ln $$\
ln \lim_{x \to 0} = {\cos x - 1 \over x} = 0
ln $$
